<paragraph id="BD863C48806B0305197EA14B66647BDC" pageId="0" pageNumber="9649">Costa Rica, ACG (Prov. Guanacaste), 1460 m</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9AC32EBDAEA298365EDF8D3CCCF80A47" pageId="0" pageNumber="9649" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="5E0A00A9A66590E01501152C61BA0832" pageId="0" pageNumber="9649">Ecology</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FF77B8F299D53AF6E19CE6C91DB78EA1" pageId="0" pageNumber="9649">
<taxonomicName id="7465BCCB13AA9095059B39B7E6247D70" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Uramya" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Uramya penicillata" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="9649" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penicillata">Uramya penicillata</taxonomicName>
has been reared only once, from an 
<taxonomicName id="E20670B049563E67112905D1F7D2DC8B" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Isochaetes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Isochaetes dwagsi" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="9649" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dwagsi">Isochaetes dwagsi</taxonomicName>
Corrales &amp; Epstein (
<taxonomicName id="EB3AA5B8FE7CF4E3878B53DE4B6619D8" family="Limacodidae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="9649" rank="family">Limacodidae</taxonomicName>
) caterpillar found in cloud forest. 
<taxonomicName id="4BD0C777C1B0C2D2AE966EC7FB121611" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Isochaetes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Isochaetes dwagsi" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="9649" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dwagsi">Isochaetes dwagsi</taxonomicName>
has been reared 503 times from sibling and non-sibling groups in ACG.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
